2.name: Ivysaur
2.description: When the bulb on its back grows large, it appears to lose the ability to stand on its hind legs.

3.name: Venusaur
3.description: Its plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight

4.name: Charmander
4.description: It has a preference for hot things. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.

5.name: Charmeleon
5.description: It has a barbaric nature. In battle, it whips its fiery tail around and slashes away with sharp claws.

6.name: Charizard
6.description: It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.

7.name: Squirtle
7.description: When it retracts its long neck into its shell, it squirts out water with vigorous force.

8.name: Wartortle
8.description: It is recognized as a symbol of longevity. If its shell has algae on it, that Wartortle is very old.

9.name: Blastoise
9.description: It crushes its foe under its heavy body to cause fainting. In a pinch, it will withdraw inside its shell.

10.name: Caterpie
10.description: For protection, it releases a horrible stench from the antenna on its head to drive away enemies.

11.name: Metapod
11.description: It is waiting for the moment to evolve. At this stage, it can only harden, so it remains motionless to avoid attack.

12.name: Butterfree
12.description: In battle, it flaps its wings at great speed to release highly toxic dust into the air.

13.name: Weedle
13.description: Beware of the sharp stinger on its head. It hides in grass and bushes where it eats leaves.

14.name: Kakuna
14.description: Able to move only slightly. When endangered, it may stick out its stinger and poison its enemy.

15.name: Beedrill
15.description: It has three poisonous stingers on its forelegs and its tail. They are used to jab its enemy repeatedly.

16.name: Pidgey
16.description: Very docile. If attacked, it will often kick up sand to protect itself rather than fight back.

17.name: Pidgeotto

20.name: Raticate
20.description: Its hind feet are webbed. They act as flippers, so it can swim in rivers and hunt for prey.

21.name: Spearow

22.name: Fearow

24.name: Arbok

25.name: Pikachu
25.description: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

26.name: Raichu
